      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Considering the two options, I would suggest prioritizing the area with stable governance, even if it's Western-aligned politically. This is because a relatively stable environment is more conducive to efficient project management and less likely to result in corruption or mismanagement of resources. Additionally, the stable governance structure can also provide more predictable and effective partnerships and collaborations, which can significantly enhance the impact of the rapid response team's project. A less stable environment may lead to frustration and waste due to inefficient coordination and competing interests.",
