    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that stability is easier for a quick rollout, but isnt that kind of a bias? like, isn't it true that regions with post-colonial histories or ethnic tensions are inherently way harder to work with regarding corruption? wouldn't a team there just spend more time fighting the local systems than actually helping people?",
